%N A123956 Triangle of coefficients of polynomials P(k) = 2*X*P(k - 1) - P(k - 2), P(0) = -1, P(1) = 1 + X, with twisted signs.
%C A123956 Up to signs also the coefficients of polynomials y(n+1) = y(n-1) - 2*h*y(n), arising when the ODE y' = -y is numerically solved with the leapfrog (a.k.a. two-step Nystr√∂m) method, with y(0) = 1, y(1) = 1 - h. In this case, the coefficients are negative exactly for the odd powers of h. - _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 30 2022
